set

public void set(java.lang.String s)
         throws java.rmi.RemoteException
Stores the given String and replicates it if another ReplicatedString has been set by using replicateAt(ReplicatedString). The given String may be null. If there is a ring (e.g. this object is it's own replicant's replicant) recurvive replicating stops once all replicants have been updated avoiding endless recursion.

Specified by:
set in interface ReplicatedString
Parameters:
s - the string to be stored and replicated.
Throws:
java.rmi.RemoteException

replicateAt

public void replicateAt(ReplicatedString rs)
Sets the ReplicatedString where any String given as parameter for set(String) should be replicated. The Object may be null causing no replication.

Specified by:
replicateAt in interface ReplicatedString
Parameters:
rs - the ReplicatedString where the String should be replicated at.
